      "id": "mnswhso8",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>RMgI when treated with ice cold water liberated a gas which occupied $1.4 \\mathrm{dm}^3 / \\mathrm{g}$ at STP. The gas produced is further reacted with iodine in presence of $\\mathrm{HIO}_3$ to give compound $(\\mathrm{X})$. Compound $(\\mathrm{X})$ in presence of Na and dry ether produced compound $(\\mathrm{Y})$. Molar mass of compound $(\\mathrm{Y})$ is $\\_\\_\\_\\_$ $\\mathrm{g} \\mathrm{mol}^{-1}$. (Nearest integer)</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 3 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1moabn7ol/e6faf49b-2b50-407e-9c12-63a03557e6f0/f926fd50-3e6f-11f1-a6eb-e1754c387608/file-6y3zli1moabn7om.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1moabn7ol/e6faf49b-2b50-407e-9c12-63a03557e6f0/f926fd50-3e6f-11f1-a6eb-e1754c387608/file-6y3zli1moabn7om.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Given that the gas produced by treating RMgI with ice-cold water occupies a volume of $1.4 \\, \\mathrm{dm}^3$ per gram at STP.</p>\n<p>At STP, one mole of any gas occupies $22.4 \\, \\mathrm{dm}^3$. So, the molar mass of the gas can be calculated as:</p>\n<p>$$ \\text{Molar mass} = \\frac{22.4}{1.4} \\approx 16 $$</p>\n<p>This shows that the gas produced is methane, $\\mathrm{CH_4}$.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 3 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1moabpa09/db410c1d-fd51-44c9-823f-44487eaeebec/3290dd90-3e70-11f1-a6eb-e1754c387608/file-6y3zli1moabpa0a.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1moabpa09/db410c1d-fd51-44c9-823f-44487eaeebec/3290dd90-3e70-11f1-a6eb-e1754c387608/file-6y3zli1moabpa0a.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>The methane formed reacts with iodine in the presence of $\\mathrm{HIO_3}$ to form methyl iodide ($\\mathrm{CH_3I}$), which is compound $(\\mathrm{X})$.</p>\n<p>When $\\mathrm{CH_3I}$ is treated with sodium metal in dry ether, a coupling reaction (Wurtz reaction) occurs, forming ethane ($\\mathrm{C_2H_6}$), which is compound $(\\mathrm{Y})$.</p>\n<p>The molar mass of ethane is:</p>\n<p>$$ \\text{Molar mass of } \\mathrm{C_2H_6} = (2 \\times 12) + (6 \\times 1) = 30 \\, \\mathrm{g \\, mol^{-1}} $$</p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Haloalkanes and Haloarenes"
    },
